,Recommended,245300,32745963,Posted: 24 June,all,P3T3R,"While this game has it's obvious flaws, with things such as an absolutley horrible camera that at times decides to go wherever it wants, the lack of Co-Op in this port of the game, and at times wonky physics, if you can let yourself get past those things, and really immerse yourself into this game, you'll find that there's actually a LOT to enjoy about this game. It's a must have for Disney fans both big and small, as it lets you see into the world of the forgotten, and relive some of the first moments in Disney history. Oh, and I forgot to mention - this aint just some cheesy, cute, Disney adventure, oh no no no.. NOT BY A LONG SHOT! The world of Wasteland is a much darker, sinister, twisted version of the Disney we all know and love, complete with broken, withered down animatronic versions of Mickey's pals like Goofy and Donald... All in all, it's a game that if it had a bit more development time, could have been a far greater game than it turned out being, but it's still VERY enjoyable as is, and has a lore unlike anything else Disney you've seen before... It's Disney at it's darkest, that's for sure! But that's what makes it interesting!"
