76561198120443172,Recommended,245300,30905921,Posted: 2 April,all,Bladez,"This was a pretty good sequel that seemed to improve upon the first game, a little.  I enjoyed the replayability of both games.  However, this sequel really didn't add anything new in that regards, just the same old same old.  Epic Mickey 2 really felt like Epic Mickey 1 with added levels.  This was not a bad thing, though, since I really enjoyed the first game and wanted to experience more of it immediately after I finished.  The graphics were bright and colorful and looked like a modern Disney cartoon with some old school scenes mixed in for nostalgia.  Using Oswald was nice, but felt unpolished and unecessary.  This game ran without any glitches or technical issues on my Intel Core i5 Toshiba PC.  In addition, my Xbox One controller made game play a lot easier and less frustrating than using the keyboard.  Overall, Epic Mickey 2 is a solid adventure/platformer game, just don't expect anything groundbreaking with this sequel.  If you enjoyed the first game and just want more of it to play, then buy it."
