 done this practice MUCH better than Epic Mickey, because in this game, your choices don't really matter. If you pick the good choice, you are praised as a hero in the end. If you pick the bad choice, you are praised as a hero in the end. Though that doesn't really take away from the over all enjoyment of the fight. Another thing I liked was the enviroment. If you didn't know, the world is pretty much a destroyed Disneyland, however, the first game did this much better. On consoles this was an over all decent game, on PC however, it is a bad game. So if you want to play one of these games, GET THE THE FIRST ONE, or purchase this game on consoles. I still do recommend getting the first one, because it is a pretty good game, and it will help you understand this one better.Consoles: 3/5PC: 2/5Not recommended unless you are a fan of the original game, or if you are interested in Disney history."
